Responsibilities
Complete and correct documentation is received, understood, communicated to and fulfilled by the supplier in all details, Approved samples availableProduction Risk Assessment done and process control implementedThe product is tested, approved and documentedZero series and First delivery inspection completed and approvedEvaluating potential new supplier’s production facilities and Quality systemSupport the supplier to implement and maintain Quality Systems (ISQAP)/IKEA working methodsCommunicate and secure changes in product requirements, production changes and working methodsResponsible for product documentationAnalyze data and take corrective action together with teamWork with tools like Master file etcSupport centre on all initiativesUnderstanding of IKEA & relevant working methods and processes Requirements: Graduated from Technical UniversitiesChemical or Textile background is an advantage1 year of working experience is preferableHave good communication in both written and spoken EnglishGood competence in technical drawing, documentation and communicationAble to work independently and as part of a teamHigh level of responsibility GROWING TOGETHERIKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global marketplace. And as the world’s leader at life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us. Please send your complete resume latest 10 May 2014To the following addresserecruitment.indonesia@ikea.comVisit IKEA.COM
